  <prompt>
    Manually smoke-test the FilePreviewDialog "Send by Email" flow end-to-end in the dev environment, verifying the migration from Wave 3 is functionally correct.

    Test scenario:
    1. Sign into LegalWorkspace in dev
    2. Navigate to a Matter (or other parent record) with at least one attached `sprk_document`
    3. Open the document via FilePreview surface
    4. Click the "Send by Email" action
    5. Verify: the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` opens with the previewed file pre-attached
    6. Fill: To = a test recipient address, Subject = "Wave 3 smoke test", Body = any non-empty text
    7. Click Send
    8. Verify: success Fluent toast appears in FilePreview parent; dialog closes
    9. Verify in Dataverse: outbound `sprk_communication` record created with `statuscode = Sent`, `sprk_internetmessageid` populated (Wave 0 task 003 outcome), correct attachment linked

    Failure scenarios to also test:
    - Send with no recipient → validation error appears via canonical wrapper (no inline error rendering in FilePreview)
    - Send with malformed recipient → canonical validation code triggers
    - Network failure scenario (simulated if possible) → `onError` receives `SendCommunicationError`; banner appears with `correlationId`

    Document all results in `notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md` per CLAUDE.md test-results convention.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    QA / smoke-test engineer authoritative on Spaarke dev environment flows. Familiar with LegalWorkspace navigation, FilePreview surface, Dataverse record verification, and the canonical Communication architecture's expected behavior.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The FilePreviewDialog → SendEmailDialog → outbound `sprk_communication` round-trip is verified working in dev. Smoke results documented in `notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md` including: positive test pass/fail, validation error tests, error path test, screenshots (optional but recommended), outbound record GUID for audit traceability.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Wave 3 migration of FilePreviewDialog (task 051) replaced inline `fetch` with the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` wrapper. The functional correctness of this migration cannot be inferred from build/lint/adr-check — only an end-to-end smoke test against a real dev environment can confirm.

      Key behaviors to verify:
      - The wrapper opens correctly when triggered from FilePreview
      - The previewed file is pre-attached (via `attachmentSources` config in task 051)
      - The recipient field accepts and validates emails per the canonical contract (FR-05)
      - Send succeeds → success Fluent toast + `onSent` callback fires + dialog closes
      - Send fails (validation) → typed validation errors surface via canonical wrapper (FR-08)
      - Send fails (server error) → `SendCommunicationError` reaches FilePreview's `onError`, banner displays `correlationId`
      - Outbound `sprk_communication` record has `sprk_internetmessageid` populated (verifies Wave 0 task 003 + Wave 3 integration in same flow)

      The dev environment URL comes from `notes/wave-3-deploy.md` (produced by task 054).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/wave-3-deploy.md (dev environment URL from task 054)</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md (NEW — smoke result)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (the migrated file under test)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Acceptance: "FilePreview file-email flow works end-to-end in dev." This task is the verification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Error path uses typed `SendCommunicationError`; verify in error scenario test (step 8 below) that `correlationId` is captured and displayed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Success / error UI uses Fluent v9 chrome (toast + banner). Verify visually.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Verify NO inline `fetch` fires from the migrated flow — observe Network panel in browser DevTools; only `/api/communications/send` request from the canonical wrapper's `sendCommunication()` should appear.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test results MUST be documented in `notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md`. PR description summarizes pass/fail status.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
