  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `notes/wave-3-deploy.md` to confirm dev environment URL and that deploy succeeded.</step>
    <step order="2">Set up the test data: identify (or create) a Matter in dev with at least one attached `sprk_document`. Note the Matter GUID + document name.</step>
    <step order="3">Positive test: open the document in FilePreview → click "Send by Email" → verify canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` opens with the file pre-attached → fill To/Subject/Body → click Send → verify success toast → confirm dialog closes.</step>
    <step order="4">Dataverse verification: query `sprk_communication` for the record just created. Verify: `statuscode = Sent` (or transition state), `sprk_internetmessageid` populated (or warn-logged failure if step 4 returned a known-issue case from Wave 0 task 003), correct attachment associated. Record the new `sprk_communicationid` GUID in smoke notes.</step>
    <step order="5">Validation test 1: open dialog again → leave To empty → click Send → verify FR-08 canonical `TO_REQUIRED` error renders in canonical wrapper (not as inline FilePreview error).</step>
    <step order="6">Validation test 2: open dialog → fill To with `not-a-valid-email` → click Send → verify FR-08 `TO_INVALID_EMAIL` error renders.</step>
    <step order="7">Network panel check: during positive test (step 3), open browser DevTools Network tab. Confirm: exactly ONE POST request to `/api/communications/send` originating from the canonical wrapper. No other `communications/send` requests from FilePreview itself.</step>
    <step order="8">Optional: simulate error path (e.g., disable network mid-send OR send with intentionally invalid recipient that triggers server-side rejection). Verify: `SendCommunicationError` surfaces in `onError`; FilePreview displays error banner with `correlationId`.</step>
    <step order="9">Compile results into `notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md` with structure:
      <code>
      # Wave 3 FilePreview Smoke Test
      Date: [date]
      Tester: [name]
      Environment: [dev URL from wave-3-deploy.md]

      ## Positive flow
      - Result: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
      - sprk_communicationid: [GUID]
      - sprk_internetmessageid populated: yes / no
      - Notes: ...

      ## Validation tests
      - TO_REQUIRED: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL
      - TO_INVALID_EMAIL: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL

      ## Error path
      - SendCommunicationError surfaces: ✅ PASS / ❌ FAIL / SKIPPED
      - correlationId displayed: yes / no

      ## Network observation
      - Single POST to /api/communications/send: ✅ confirmed / ❌ multiple requests / ❌ inline fetch detected

      ## Issues / Defects
      [List any defects to file]
      </code>
    </step>
    <step order="10">If smoke test fails on positive flow OR network observation reveals inline fetch: escalate to tasks 051 / 053 / 050 for fix. Do NOT mark task 055 complete until smoke passes (or owner approves a known-deferred defect).</step>
    <step order="11">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 055 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (060 — Wave 4 start).</step>
  </steps>

