  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Positive flow: send-email from FilePreview succeeds → outbound `sprk_communication` record created with `statuscode = Sent`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`sprk_internetmessageid` populated on outbound record (or documented warn-logged failure per FR-22 best-effort).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Validation tests: `TO_REQUIRED` and `TO_INVALID_EMAIL` errors surface via canonical wrapper.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Network panel confirms ONE POST to `/api/communications/send` per send action; no inline fetch from FilePreview.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/test-results/055-filepreview-smoke.md` documents all test results with pass/fail and traceable record GUIDs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`TASK-INDEX.md` marks task 055 ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `sprk_internetmessageid` verification (step 4) tests cross-wave integration: Wave 0 task 003 (server post-send capture) + Wave 3 (client wrapper) together. If the field is null on the outbound record, root-cause to Wave 0 first (server didn't capture) before suspecting Wave 3.

    Browser automation: if the `ui-test` skill / Chrome integration is available, the test can be partially scripted. Otherwise, manual browser testing is acceptable for a smoke test. Document the testing mode in smoke notes.

    The `notes/test-results/` directory may not exist yet — create it. Per CLAUDE.md §3, `notes/` is project-internal and NOT subject to the `.claude/` write boundary.

    This task gates the start of Wave 4 (task 060). Do not advance to Wave 4 with an unresolved Wave 3 smoke failure — the SummarizeFilesDialog migration in Wave 4 follows the same canonical pattern, so a Wave 3 defect will likely manifest in Wave 4 too.
  </notes>

